+ # Deployment Simulation
+
+ ##  Jenkins pipeline -Simulated Deployment
+ you will learn how to **simulate deployment to different environments**
+
+ pipeline {
+     agent any
+     parameters {
+         choice(name:-'ENVIRNOMENT'. choice: ['dev'. 'staging'. 'pord']. description: Deployment Envirnoment )
+       }
+       environment {
+           INSTITUTE_NAME = "Pathnex"
+       }
+       stages {
+          stage('Deploy') {
+             steps {
+                 sh 'echo "Deploying $INSTITUTE_NAME application to $ENVIRONMENT"'
+              }
+          {
+      {
+  }
+
+ ##  Gitlab CI - Deployment Simulation
+ you will learn how to **simulate deployment in Gitlab CI using environment variable**.
+
+ stages:
+   - deploy
+
+ variables1;
+   INSTITUTE_NAME: "Pathnex"
+   ENVIRONMENT: "staging"
+
+ deploy:
+   stage: deploy
+   image: alpine:latest
+   cript:
+      - echo "Deployment $INSTITUTE_NAME application to $ENVIRONMENT"
